![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Properties**

**Description**

**Code**

Unique identifier of the Serializer. The identifier establishes the Serializer during print spool generation.

**Name**

Assign a name to the Serializer without the restrictions imposed by the code.

**Encoding**

Set the Serializer encoding, also used for non UTF-8 indexes.

- Central European (1250)

- Western (1252)

- Turkish (1254)

**Description**

You may assign a description to the Serializer for rapid indication of its main functions.

**Calculate personalized fill pages as personalized pages**

This option allows to count the fill pages that include content as personalized or fill pages in the statistics of the run.

Modifying the properties of the Serializer

-  Enter the text of choice for the **Name**. 

-  Enter the text for the **Description**.

## **Modifying the Serializer code**
- Click **Change... **next to the Serializer code.

- Enter the new code in the **Edit serializer **window

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Apply** or press **Enter** to confirm the modification and close the window

- Click **Cancel **to cancel the modification procedure and close the window.

> Warning

The Serializer modification window performs a validation on the code entered. If the identifier field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Project, the modification is not possible.
